Everybody has to have a good local place for dinner when you just want good food at a reasonable place. I have my pizza place, my take out deli, Hispanic and now I have my Thai place. It is newly opened in a strip mall. The food is traditional Thai and straight forward and delicious. It is a "Mom and Pop" shop with a small seating area and a great takeout. They can regulate the spice level that pleases my MIL (mild) to me ( Thai Spicy) . If you are in the area this is a great place for great food

My family and I decided to stop here for lunch after an emergency room visit from Methodist hospital. There were for adults and 2 toddlers in our party. The gentleman who greeted us asked if we had a reservation and we all stared at him in confusion because it was only 6 of us in total in closing the 2 toddlers. We said no and eventually was seated. We finished our meal a little after 2pm to recieve a bill with the gratuity already added in. To my knowledge, that's only suppose to happen when there is a party of 10 or more after 9pm where NY gratuity is automatically added to the bill. Not only did they seem as if they would turn us away in the beginning for so called not having a reservation but then in my opinion, u racially profiled my family assuming that we probably wouldn't tip the waiter by doing something like that. I have been coming to this place for yrs and never have experienced anything like this. They have officially lost me as a customer.

Ambiance- cool/okay . Waiters- pleasant and accommodating... but read further. Food- less than meh. I initially ordered fried tilapia with chili sauce, which I’ve had before at other restaurants- (lunch menu). This presentation however was sooo unappetizing. It looked like guck. Thick pieces of super soft rectangular fish plopped on a plate with heavy sauce. And the plate... why on earth would you serve ADULTS on thick, ceramic portioned plates? I’d swear I was at a Medieval times show, expecting knights to begin jousting any moment now. Giving me cutlery was a step up! I returned the fish and opted for chicken pad Thai. Again, the thick 6 section plate comes out with pad Thai in one section. What was in the other section you ask- looked like paint chips. And when I told the waitress I was given an unclean plate, she reached over me, over the food and with her fingers, touched the substance to tell me it was flour. W. T. F. Fast forward to the bill, after I signed it, the waiter asked me to give him a tip!(with a smile). I gave a dollar, .50 more than was deserved and Ubered to my fav Thai spot immediately after. Never. Again.

I traveled across Brooklyn today to have dinner at my favorite restaurant. While eating, I observed my waiter picking his nose. I stopped and watched until he was done (disgusted) to see if he would wash his hands after. He picked up a piece of tissue, brushed his finger across it, threw it in the trash, and without washing his hands, proceeded out of the kitchen and began placing plates on the table. ( He was setting the tables) I called him over and asked if he'd washed his hands (already knowing he didn't, because i watched him) and he said,  "yes I did". He walked over to the hostess, told her what happened and they looked at me and started to laugh. I stood up, walked over, told her what i saw, and she said to me " yes, he washed his hands" I said to her " I saw him with my own eyes and he DID NOT WASH HIS HANDS". She says to me "yes he did" I looked at her as if she was crazy and walked out pissed off. This is the first review I've ever written for an establishment.
